[ANALYSIS]
The experiment `bow_opt_20260514_172430_run_05` using a Bag of Words (BoW) architecture achieved a respectable F1 score of 0.708 and an accuracy of 0.7525, indicating that the model performed reasonably well on the validation set. The use of TF-IDF vectorization with a maximum n-gram length of 2 contributed positively to the results, as did the optimal threshold setting at 0.43. However, the experiment could have benefited from a more extensive hyperparameter search, particularly for the regularization parameter `logreg_c`, which was set to its default value of 1.0. For the next run, consider expanding the range and granularity of the hyperparameter grid to explore different values of `logreg_c` as well as other parameters like `max_features` and `min_df`. Additionally, incorporating more sophisticated feature engineering techniques or exploring alternative models could further enhance performance.